<HR><H2>Ports</H2>
<H3>daemon@ATHENA.MIT.EDU (Wed May 18 19:42:24 1994
)</H3>
<PRE>
Date: Wed, 18 May 1994 17:37:45 -0600 (MDT)
From: the Lyncx &lt;BRANDON@cc.usu.edu&gt;
To: coldstuff@MIT.EDU
X-Vms-To: COLDSTUFF

The idea would be to standardize ports, so its just known that a N type server
would be on the same port for the same application.  The idea of connecting
thorugh the same port for _everything_ is bad in my opinion.  We can use more
ports, why not use them?  It would mean less complicated code in the end, and a
much more simple design.
</PRE>
